Main firewall of a medium-sized company. The company wishes to remain anonymous.
They donated their full, uncensored dumps. Thank you very much.

All rules are left as they are. No addresses were anonymized.

Setup:
 * eth0 connects the local 172.16.2.0/24 network.
 * ppp0 is the uplink to the internet.


The administrator explained that parts of the ruleset were inspired by
  https://wiki.archlinux.org/index.php/Simple_stateful_firewall

Archive:
  https://wiki.archlinux.org/index.php?title=Simple_stateful_firewall&oldid=418422
  https://web.archive.org/web/20150214141034/https://wiki.archlinux.org/index.php/Simple_Stateful_Firewall

The iptables-save outputs were generated on my local machine, the packet counters do not correspond to those of the original firewall.


